12/01/2011
ANKARA, Turkey -- Hundreds of Kurds clashed with police in southeast Turkey on Tuesday (January 11th) during a protest against the trial of over 150 Kurds charged with links to Kurdish rebels.
Police used smoke grenades to disperse the demonstrators in the town of Cizre, near the Iraqi border.
No injuries were reported.
In other news, five Turkish officers died late Monday when a military helicopter on a training flight crashed outside a village near Ankara.
The General Staff announced on Tuesday that an investigation is under way to determine the cause of the crash.
(Hurriyet, AP, Dogan - 11/01/11)
